FREE Dining & Drinks!

FREE Dining & Drinks on your 2025 Walt Disney World Holiday!

Don't miss our incredible offer for Summer 2025!

Make 2025 your year to experience the wonder of Walt Disney World Resort in Florida. Book by 31st March 2025 for arrivals between 27th May - 30th September 2025 and you'll enjoy FREE Dining & Drinks (selected meals, excluding gratuities)! This incredible offer is available during summer school holidays.

Download our handy guide to learn more (PDF)

How Can I Benefit from this Package Offer?

Step 1: Choose a participating Disney Resort hotel for a 4-night minimum stay

Step 2: Add one of our Park Hopper Ticket options for a minimum of 5 days

Step 3: Book your package to enjoy FREE Dining & Drinks (including selected meals, excluding gratuities)

Book by 31st March 2025 from as little as €65 deposit per person!

What's Included with FREE Dining & Drinks?

With this amazing offer you'll benefit from our one of our magical Dining Plans included in your package, based on your chosen Resort hotel.

With meals and drinks included on every day of your stay, with our Dining Plans enjoy peace of mind with prepaid meals and snacks without compromising on quality, flexibility or choice. There's something to delight every taste, from quick bites to fine cuisine - all you have to focus on is the fun!

Disney Quick-Service Dining Plan

Value & Moderate Resort hotel bookings

For families on the go, this is a fast and easy meal plan option - especially when you have little ones in tow!

Available at 90+ locations.

Per Guest (aged 3+), per night of your stay:

  • 2 Quick-Service meals
  • 1 non-alcoholic/alcoholic drink per meal
  • 1 selected snack or drink
  • Resort-refillable mug

Savings of €55.99 per adult, per day

Disney Quick-Service Dining Plan

Disney Dining Plan

Deluxe Resort hotels & Deluxe Villa bookings

The perfect choice to savour special family moments over sit-down meals and watch the kids light up during Character Dining!

Available at 170+ locations.

Per Guest (aged 3+), per night of your stay:

  • 1 Quick-Service meal
  • 1 Table-Service meal
  • 1 non-alcoholic/alcoholic drink per meal
  • 1 selected snack or drink
  • Resort-refillable mug

Savings of €89.99 per adult, per day

Disney Dining Plan

Relax in fantastical settings that bring your favourite Disney and Pixar stories to life

Get extra time to play with extended time in the Theme Parks

Experience enchantment around every corner – you may even spot some familiar Disney friends!

Enjoy complimentary transportation across the Resort, including monorail and the Disney Skyliner

Find something that suits you, with room options for 5+ Guests

Explore Walt Disney World Theme Parks With Park Hopper Tickets

You'll enjoy FREE Dining & Drinks when you add one of our magical Park Hopper Ticket options to your booking, for a minimum of 5 days.

Park Hopper Ticket: Enjoy visiting multiple Parks on the same day during Park hours, each with their own extraordinary stories to tell.

Park Hopper Plus Ticket: Upgrade for even more magic - enjoy unlimited daily admission to all 4 Theme Parks during Park hours, plus Water Park fun and more!

Magic Kingdom Park

At Magic Kingdom Park, enter a land where pure fantasy reigns and live happily ever after.

  • Whistle while you work as you race through a shimmering diamond mine on Seven Dwarfs Mine Train.
  • Go on a high-speed chase across a world with no horizons on TRON Lightcycle / Run, one of the fastest coasters at any Disney Park!
  • Drop on by for an all-swingin' extravaganza on the NEW Tiana's Bayou Adventure - featuring a thrilling crescendo with a 50-foot drop!

Magic Kingdom Park

Disney's Hollywood Studios

Become the hero of your ultimate adventure at Disney's Hollywood Studios.

  • Adventure far, far away as you fly the famous starship and battle against the First Order at Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge.
  • Play big in Andy's backyard at Toy Story Land! Spring into the action on Slinky Dog Dash and meet Woody, Buzz Lightyear and Jessie.
  • Lurking in the shadows of Sunset Boulevard, join the infamous Disney Villains with their fiendish stage show - debuting summer 2025!

Disney's Hollywood Studios

EPCOT

Spark your imagination at EPCOT, where it's fun to do the impossible.

  • Rock out on an intergalatic chase through space and blast into the action on Guardians of the Galaxy: Cosmic Rewind.
  • Voyage to wintery Arendelle with Elsa, Anna, Olaf and Frozen friends on the musical Frozen Ever After, sure to melt the coldest of hearts.
  • Discover the playful personality of water along a lush outdoor trail with the NEW Journey of Water, Inspired by Moana.

EPCOT

Disney's Animal Kingdom Theme Park

At Disney's Animal Kingdom Theme Park, find a natural wonderland alive with magic.

  • Discover a world beyond belief in Pandora - The World of Avatar, soaring on the back of your very own mountain banshee.
  • Roar along with the flocks of the Pride Lands in Festival of the Lion King, with songs, pageantry and puppetry.
  • Take a walk on the wildside as you encounter giraffes, elephants, lions and more as you tour a lush savanna on Kilimanjaro Safaris.

Disney's Animal Kingdom Theme Park

Spread the Cost with Flexible Instalments

Simply put down a deposit from just €65 per person, then pay the rest by your balance due date – you decide how much and when, with no fees and no interest.

  • Enjoy greater flexibility, with the amounts and number of instalments up to you
  • The price you see is the price you pay, with no fees or interest
  • Book early and enjoy a greater choice of package options, with no need to pay your full balance immediately
  • Payments aren’t automatic, you choose when to pay – as long as it’s before your balance due date

Terms and Conditions

Terms and conditions apply; click here for details. Valid for new bookings only. Subject to availability.

1. Free Dining and Drinks Offer

1.1. Book between 7th January 2025 and 31st March 2025 (inclusive) a minimum of 4 and a maximum of 14 consecutive nights stay in one of the participating Walt Disney World Resort Hotels (Disney Resort) and a minimum 5 Day and maximum 10 Day Park Hopper or Park Hopper Plus Ticket on arrival dates between 27th May and 30th September 2025 (inclusive) and receive:

a) A Quick Service Dining Plan if you stay in a participating Value or Moderate Disney Resort;

or

b) A Disney Dining Plan if you stay in a participating Deluxe Disney Resort or Deluxe Villa Resort as specified in more detail below.

The number and type of rooms allocated to this offer is limited and subject to room availability. This Package offer cannot be combined with other available Walt Disney Travel Company offers unless specified in these terms.

Free Dining and Drinks Offer excludes gratuities. An 18% gratuity will automatically be added to the bill for parties of six or more.

The following entitlements are included in the relevant Disney Dine plans:

a) Disney Quick-Service Dining Plan includes: 2 Quick-Service Meals, 1 non-alcoholic/alcoholic beverage per meal, 1 Selected Snack per person per night's stay and 1 Refillable Resort Mug per person.

b) Disney Dining Plan includes: 1 Quick-Service Meal, 1 Table-Service Meal, 1 non-alcoholic/alcoholic beverage per meal, 1 Selected Snack per person per night's stay and 1 Refillable Resort Mug per person.

Advance restaurant reservations are strongly recommended and may be required at some Table-Service restaurants participating in the Disney Dining Plan. Florida law permits the sale and service of alcohol products only to persons 21 years of age and older. The operators of the Walt Disney World Resort participate in Florida's Responsible Vendor program, and servers will verify age by requesting acceptable identification. Please note that all persons visiting from outside of the United States are required to present both a valid passport as well as another form of government-issued photo ID from their country of origin.

1.1.2. A Quick Service Dining Plan is included at the following Value and Moderate Disney Resorts:

Disney’s All-Star Movies Resort, Disney’s All-Start Music Resort, Disney’s All-Star Sports Resort, Disney’s Pop Century Resort, Disney Art of Animation Resort. Disney's Caribbean Beach Resort, Disney’s Coronado Springs Resort, Disney’s Port Orleans Resort – Riverside, Disney’s Port Orleans Resort – French Quarter.

1.1.3. A Disney Dine Plan is included at the following Deluxe Disney and Deluxe Villa Resorts:

Disney Animal Kingdom Lodge (excluding Savannah View 1 Bedroom Suite - Club Level, 2 Bedroom Suites - Club Level, Royal Assante Presidential Suite), Disney’s Polynesian Village Resort (excluding 1 Bedroom Suite - Club Level, Ambassador Vice Presidential Suite - Club Level), Disney’s Grand Floridian and Spa (excluding 1 & 2 Bedroom Suites - Club Level, Disney Suite - Club Level, 1 Bedroom Victorian Suite - Club Level), Disney’s Wilderness Lodge, Disney’s Beach Club Resort (excluding 1&2 Bedroom Suites - Club Level, Newport Presidential Suite - Club Level), Disney’s Yacht Club Resort (excluding Turret Suite - Club Level, 2 Bedroom Suite Club Level, Commodore Vice Presidential Suite - Club Level), Disney’s Boardwalk Inn, Disney’s Contemporary Resort (excluding Theme Park View 1 Bedroom Suite – Club Level, Garden Wing 1 Bedroom Suite - Club Level, Theme Park View Presidential Suite - Club Level), Disney’s BoardWalk Villas, Boulder Ridge Villas at Disney’s Wilderness Lodge, Disney’s Beach Club Villas, Disney’s Saratoga Springs Resort and Spa (excluding 3 Bedroom Treehouse Villa, 3 Bedroom Grand Villa and 3 Bedroom Grand Villa Preferred), Bay Lake Tower at Disney’s Contemporary Resort, Disney’s Animal Kingdom Villas – Kidani Village (excluding 3 Bedroom Grand Villa – Savannah View), The Villas at Grand Floridian Spa and Resort (excluding3 Bedroom Grand Villa - Preferred View), Copper Creek Villas & Cabins at Disney’s Wilderness Lodge (excluding 3 Bedroom Grand Villa, 2 Bedroom Cabin), Disney’s Riviera Resort (excluding 3 Bedroom Grand Villa), Disney’s Old Key West (excluding 3 Bedroom Grand Villa)

2. Dining Plan restrictions

2.1. A minimum of 4 and a maximum of 14 consecutive nights stay and a minimum 5 Day and maximum 10 Day Park Hopper or Park Hopper Plus Ticket must be selected for all members of the party on the booking who are aged 3 and over at the time of travel and purchased at the same time for the entire duration of the booking to receive the Free Dining offer. Meals are non-transferable between party members and expire at midnight on the Disney Resort reservation checkout date.

Upgrades to Free Disney Dining Plans must be selected for all members of the party for the full duration of the stay depending on the type of the participating Disney Resort. Children aged 3-9 inclusive (at time of visit) must order from the children’s menu where available. Disney Dining Plans are not valid for children under 3 years. Please note that the Disney Dining Plan entitlements for 2025 arrivals and locations may be subject to change. Disney Dining Plan meals provide everyone in the party (ages 3 and over) a specific number of meals and snacks per day per person based on the number of nights of a Disney Resort stay. Certain menu items may incur an additional cost. An additional form of payment is required if gratuities are added and if a credit card has not been provided at check-in for charging incidentals and other expenses. Operating hours, menus, Characters, entertainment, participating locations, components and terms are subject to change without notice. The Walt Disney World Resort shall not be responsible for the non-utilization of package components due to refurbishing, capacity, closures, inclement weather or any circumstance beyond their control. For information on Disney Dining Plans visit www.disneyholidays.co.uk/walt-disney-world/dining-plans/ or www.disneyholidays.ie/walt-disney-world/dining-plans/.

2.2. Dishes shown on disneypackages.co.uk are indicative of restaurant menus on offer, but availability may vary at time of travel. Dining plan meals and snacks are not sold separately, are non-refundable, non-transferable and have no cash value. Theme Park admission is required for some dining locations. Meals and snacks can be redeemed on any day during a stay or in any order until the number associated with the package have been depleted. All unused meals and snacks and the ability to use your refillable mug expire at midnight on the Disney Resort reservation checkout date.

Snack is a choice of ONE of the following: 20oz fountain soft drink, 20oz bottle of soft drink or water, single-serving coffee, hot chocolate, hot tea, milk, juice, popcorn scoop (single serving box), frozen ice cream novelty, popsicle or fruit bar, Mickey pretzel with cheese, funnel cake, single serving bag of snacks, piece of fruit or cup of soup at selected locations.

Where "beverages" are included for Table-Service and Quick-Service meals, Guests may choose ONE of the following: all canned and bottled single serving non-alcoholic beverages, any size single service fountain soda, all single size non-alcoholic specialty beverages (such as smoothies, milkshakes, frozen coffees, slushes). One beverage per meal. Guests 21 and older may substitute for beer, wine, mixed drinks or cocktails. Some beverages will be excluded. Novelty or souvenir cups are not included. Refillable mugs are eligible for refills from self-service beverage islands at any Disney Resort hotel Quick-Service location. Mug design shown is indicative and is subject to change.

3. Pay for your package by Instalments

Paying in Instalments – get more time to pay. Guests can choose the size and frequency of instalments for their Walt Disney World package booking subject to deposit requirements and provided the full balance is paid by the balance due date. For Walt Disney World accommodation bookings not including a flight, a deposit of €65 per person is due at the time of booking with full payment due 56 days before departure. For bookings made after this time, the full amount is due. For Walt Disney World accommodation bookings including a flight, a deposit of €185 per person is due at the time of booking with the full balance due 100 days before departure. For bookings made after this time, the full amount is due. For Walt Disney World Ticket only bookings, 100% is payable at the time of booking. For information on Paying in Instalments, please visit https://www.disneyholidays.co.uk/walt-disney-world/instalment-payments/.

†Indicative package prices and inclusions based on a 4-night stay at the respective Disney Resort hotel, including Disney's 5-Day Park Hopper Ticket, for arrival on 17th August 2025. Average price calculated by dividing the package price (€2,882 at Disney's All-Star Sports Resort, €3,541 at Disney's Port Orleans Resort – Riverside, €4,168 at Disney’s Animal Kingdom Lodge, €4,072 at Disney's Saratoga Springs Spa & Resort) by 4 people (2 adults and 2 children aged 3-9) and 4 nights. Prices are correct as of 30th December 2024. Subject to availability.

Your Privacy

Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and to change your default settings. Please be aware that blocking some types of cookies may adversely impact your experience of our site and the services we are able to offer. Using this tool will set a cookie on your device to remember your preferences, which you can change at any time. To find out more, please read our cookie policy.

Technically Necessary

Always Active

These cookies are necessary for our services to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in, accessing, searching, or discovering content, or filling in forms. You can set your browser to block, or alert you about, these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work.

Performance & Analytics

These cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site.

Functional

These cookies are used by us to detect or remember choices you make to customise your experience, such as language, location or other settings. Disabling these cookies may impact performance.

Targeting & Advertising Cookies

These cookies may be set through our site by us and/or by our advertising partners. They may be used to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant advertising on this and on other sites, as well to measure the effectiveness of our advertising campaigns. They may not store directly personal information, but instead may be based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device or be associated with your registration information. You can choose to allow these cookies or to opt out at any time.
